
1. Users App (existing)

 • Purpose: Authentication and basic user management
 • Features:
    • Email/Google/GitHub auth (using AllAuth)
    • Profile management (karma scores, achievements)
    • Private user data storage
 • Models to add:

   class UserProfile(models.Model):
       user = OneToOneField(User)
       karma = IntegerField(default=0)
       streak_count = IntegerField(default=0)


2. Posts App (new)

 • Core feature: Future plan management
 • Features:
    • Create/edit posts with deadlines
    • Status tracking (pending/completed/failed)
    • Proof submission system
 • Key models:

   class PlanPost(models.Model):
       user = ForeignKey(User)
       content = TextField()
       deadline = DateTimeField()
       status = CharField(choices=STATUS_CHOICES, default='pending')
       proof_media = ImageField(null=True, blank=True)


3. Interactions App (new)

 • Purpose: Engagement system
 • Features:
    • Believe/Doubt functionality
    • Motivation system (comments/cheers)
    • Behavioral tracking
 • Key models:

   class Interaction(models.Model):
       INTERACTION_CHOICES = [('BELIEVE', 'Believe'), ('DOUBT', 'Doubt')]
       user = ForeignKey(User)
       post = ForeignKey(PlanPost)
       interaction_type = CharField(choices=INTERACTION_CHOICES)
       motivation_text = TextField(blank=True)


4. Gamification App (new)

 • Purpose: Drive engagement metrics
 • Features:
    • Karma point calculations
    • Achievement badges
    • Leaderboard logic
 • Key components:

   class KarmaTransaction(models.Model):
       user = ForeignKey(User)
       points = IntegerField()
       source = ForeignKey(...)  # Link to post/interaction


5. Notifications App (new)

 • Purpose: Reminder system
 • Features:
    • Deadline reminders (email/push)
    • Interaction alerts
    • Karma milestone notifications
 • Integration: Use Celery for scheduled reminders

6. Teams App (new)

 • Purpose: Group accountability
 • Features:
    • Team creation
    • Group challenges
    • Collaborative karma tracking
 • Key models:

   class Team(models.Model):
       members = ManyToManyField(User)
       challenges = ForeignKey(Challenge, ...)

   class Challenge(models.Model):
       name = CharField()
       deadline = DateTimeField()


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Integration Notes:

 1 Signals: Use Django signals to trigger:
    • Karma calculations when posts are confirmed
    • Notifications when deadlines approach
    • Leaderboard updates after interactions
 2 API Structure:

   # Example endpoint for post interaction
   path('api/posts/<int:pk>/react/', PostReactView.as_view())

 3 Dependencies:

   # INSTALLED_APPS
   'allauth',              # Existing
   'allauth.socialaccount', # Existing
   'celery',               # New (for reminders)

 4 Key Relationships:

   User -> PlanPost (1:M)
   PlanPost -> Interaction (1:M)
   Interaction -> KarmaTransaction (1:1)
   Team -> Users (M:M)
   Team -> Challenge (1:M)


This structure prevents fat models, isolates business logic, and maintains RESTful endpoints. Each app can be developed/tested independently before
integration.

